<h2 id="descriptive-error-and-validation-messages">Descriptive error and validation messages</h2>

<p>Use an error message to explain why whatâ€™s been entered isnâ€™t right, and how to fix it.</p>

<p>These should only be shown if a user tries to move on to the next stage of the form, not when they select a field, are typing or move away from the field.</p>

<p>A good error message is concise, positive and specific. Avoid things like, â€˜An error occurredâ€™ or â€˜invalid information enteredâ€™. The message should make sense out of context and sound like something youâ€™d say to a user.</p>

